OUR HISTORY





Gardner Lewis Asset Management was founded in April 1990 by W. Whitfield Gardner and John L. Lewis IV.
 
The firm is rooted in the belief that a “roll-up-the-sleeves” approach to investing is the best way to uncover unrecognized opportunities. Since its inception, the firm has been privately-owned and maintains independence from any outside business affiliations or joint ventures.  Gardner Lewis is based in the Brandywine Valley with its office located in Chadds Ford, Pennsylvania.
 
Our firm fosters a team environment to provide the highest level of operational expertise and service to our clients.  From the beginning, Gardner Lewis has valued a distinctive firm culture and has focused on pursuing favorable investment outcomes through a process that is differentiated and consistent. We believe these factors are integral to the value we offer our clients.














