Gardner Lewis focuses on transformational change, where fundamental research and risk-advantaged positioning can drive favorable outcomes.
Rigorous fundamental research is the cornerstone of our investment process.
We are rooted in the belief that a "roll-up-the-sleeves" approach to investing is the best way to uncover unrecognized opportunities
Analysts, traders, and portfolio managers working together without compartmentalization fuel original thinking and form the fabric of our firm culture. 

























OUR FIRM


Gardner Lewis Asset Management is a privately-owned investment management firm located outside of Philadelphia, PA.  Since the firm’s inception in 1990, the focus of the investment team has been to seek, identify and invest in compelling opportunities for both institutions and individuals throughout the United States and abroad.








ALIGNMENT OF INTERESTS


CONSISTENT FIRM LEADERSHIP


SINGULAR INVESTMENT PHILOSOPHY


DISTINCTIVE FIRM CULTURE




Independent firm owned entirely by its investment professionals – unencumbered by distractions associated with larger organizations.
We invest alongside our clients in all that we do.


Leadership has been in place for over 20 years.
Average tenure of senior professionals is more than 15 years.


Gardner Lewis seeks to invest in differentiated opportunity sets where fundamental research and risk-advantaged positioning can drive favorable outcomes.


The Gardner Lewis Culture thrives on intellectual curiosity and teamwork.  Integrated workflow combines with a “roll-up-the-sleeves” approach towards fundamental research to fuel an environment of original thinking.







INVESTMENT PHILOSOPHY


Gardner Lewis focuses on transformational change, where fundamental research and risk-advantaged positioning can drive favorable outcomes.








TRANSFORMATIONAL CHANGE


Companies experiencing a catalyst acting as a force to drive growth or unlock value.


RISK-ADVANTAGED


We seek investment opportunities with attractive upside potential and limited or muted downside risk.










RESEARCH


Since the firm’s inception, Gardner Lewis has been dedicated to fundamentally researched investing.  We believe that fundamental work uncovers opportunity and identifies risk.











FUNDAMENTAL


In-depth work driven by the bottom-up analysis of each opportunity.  The potential of each idea is evaluated from a financial and strategic perspective and the thesis is scrutinized rigorously before and during each investment.







INTEGRATED APPROACH


We  believe in traders, analysts, and portfolio managers working together without compartmentalization.  Our integrated “team” philosophy fuels original thinking.







VARIANT PERCEPTION


What is it that we understand about this opportunity that differs from the consensus view?







INVESTMENT STRATEGIES


We offer our clients a number of investment options, each with a different focus.




MERGER ARBITRAGE


• Pure merger arbitrage
• Low volatility
• Uncorrelated
 
Seeks to produce consistent, uncorrelated returns with low volatility by investing in mergers and acquisitions.  All deals are fundamentally researched and analyzed from a strategic, regulatory, financial, and stakeholder perspective.  We believe our strict deal criteria and disciplined risk controls have allowed us to consistently deliver attractive risk-adjusted outcomes across various market cycles.




EVENT DRIVEN


• Merger arbitrage + special situations
• Full capital structure
• Hard & soft catalyst
 
Seeks to dynamically allocate capital across hard and soft catalyst opportunity sets.  The strategy attempts to pursue merger arbitrage & special situations throughout the capital structure.  The preference is for convex return profiles (focused on limiting downside while providing attractive upside potential) in every investment.  The strategy focuses on capital structure, liquidity, and risk-adjusted return analysis within each event. Events may be either positive or negative, including but not limited to corporate actions, recapitalizations, reorganization, change in industry dynamics, and/or corporate strategy change.




EQUITY


• Long/short
• Long only
• Private
 
Seeks to invest in fundamentally advantaged companies effecting disruptive innovation in an industry and those that are undergoing positive change as the result of one or more catalysts acting as a force to drive growth or unlock potential.













